Package: qualitema
Type: Package
Title: Quality of Life for EMA
Version: 0.0.100
Author: Ian M. Raugh
Maintainer: Ian M. Raugh <ian.raugh@gmail.com>
Description: A set of functions designed to make life easier in working with EMA data.
    Includes several functions that are applicable beyond EMA (ecological 
    momentary assessment) but were developed in the process of analyzing 
    EMA data. Several functions will later be split into their own 
    packages for post-hoc testing and plotting, but are kept here for 
    convenience. As this approaches readiness for general use and possible
    CRAN submission, those will be split off. While the functions should
    be stable enough for most users, their documentation is 
    under-developed and may be buggy.
License: MIT <https://cran.r-project.org/web/licenses/MIT>
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: 
    dplyr,
